Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Banana
    A Banana object contains a banana image's coordinates.
    BananaPanel1
    BananaPanel1 handles user directions for the robot's goal coordinates (in the form of dragging and dropping a banana on the screen), and controls animation of the robot in its movement towards those coordinates.
    ChargingBox
    Displays battery level in "sleep" mode.
    CurrentBox
    CurrentBox displays current and torque as an animated line graph with a double y-axis.
    Gibbot
    A Gibbot object contains data on where the robot is on the board, to be translated to user interface.
    GibbotGUI3
    GibbotGUI3 is a JFrame (window) object that runs the GUI.
    GUILayeredPane
    GUILayeredPane is the highest panel in this GUI's hierarchy (contained by an instance of a GibbotGUI3 frame).
    GUISerialPort
    Wrapper class for jssc's SerialPort; gets all data from wireless serial connection.
    GUITimer
    GUITimer is a wrapper class for Swing Timer; gets started by GibbotGUI3 and is used for animations.
    HardwareBox
    HardwareBox displays motor temperature and battery life in a bar chart graphic
    ImageHandler  
    LayoutContainerPanel
    LayoutContainerPanel is the "awake" view of the GUI.
    LayoutContainerPanel2
    This is the "asleep" view of the GUI.
    Speedometer
    Speedometer is what it sounds like; shows the linear velocity of the two links with two different colored "needles"
    TextBox
    TextBox displays the message: "real time wireless data from the gibbot" with an animated wireless signal.
